@since 0.3.26rc1

An ABC with one method `__bool__` which equals invoking `bool(self)`. To keep accordance with Python 2, there is also method `__nonzero__`, which you are encouraged to use the same way as `__bool__`. Preferred use:

```
def __bool__(self): ... # some code
def __nonzero__(self): return self.__bool__()
```

@since 0.3.27a3

A class decorator for functions, transforming them to declarations similar to classes. Example:

```
@ClassLike
def test():
    return 42

a = test() # returns 42
```
